Text.Value: Do not allow some silly, bitter complaint to taint that.
Read Gortash's thoughts again.
That is the royal 'we', I think. Little men do not like to share power.
This thing in my chest is killing me, you know. You did that.
Then why in the Nine Hells have you come back here, Karlach? What could you possibly want?!
Karlach. I was wondering when you'd come.
Dream on, Gortash. You're dead. Just like me, but sooner.
Do not squander this opportunity. It may be the last one you get.
Yet you snubbed my warning and brought my Iron Throne to ruin.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The player enters Gortash's room, and Gortash smiles wide.
EditorData.logicalname: Has stones, Orin is dead, prisoners are imprisoned

EditorData.AnimationTags: [Choices][Steel Watcher] Finally, the Steel Watcher stepw forward. It activates, looking devastatingly powerful.
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Finally, the Steel Watcher stepw forward. It activates, looking devastatingly powerful.

Text.Value: You can count on me, Karlach. I promise.
I helped you realise your potential. Look at you now, Karlach. You stand at the precipice of a new era.
First, we take Baldur's Gate, then Faerûn. All of Toril will soon follow. A thousand kingdoms, at our command.
Relinquishing the stone to him makes us servants, not allies. We should keep what we have earned.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [Choices][Banites] Several Banites step from the corner shadows, one at a time. They look fierce and dangerous.
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Several Banites step from the corner shadows, one at a time. They look fierce and dangerous.

Text.Value: I didn't enjoy watching you make a mess of our plans. It pains me to witness your potential wasted - again.
You betrayed our lord by ignoring his Chosen. You always were a fool.
I hope this girl has grown a backbone. Otherwise, I'll have to send her back where she came from.
Study Gortash again. What more can you glean?
An alliance? You must be joking.
Why in the Nine Hells have you come back here, Karlach? What could you possibly want?
How about an apology for sending me to the Hells?
And what is it you're working on, hmm? Seeding chaos upon my Iron Throne? Defying our agreement?
Karlach. You've no resonance about you at all. No Netherstones - not even Ketheric Thorm's.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Gortash raises his arm, showing his gauntlet. The Netherstone in it gleams. He lowers his arms. Then only he speaks the line... [Choices]

Text.Value: You're 'working on it' are you? You used your time to break our agreement and bring my Iron Throne to ruin.
I think I'll take that second horn of yours and use it as a goblet.
We will meet under the city and take control of the brain. Then we will take our rightful place as its rulers.
Fine. Take it.
Thanks to you, I don't hope for things anymore. I just take whatever it is I want.
Yet you've returned without Orin's. This was not the agreement.
Wouldn't that be fitting? A servant even past your dying day.
Were you hoping for something else? A word of wisdom? A hug?
You betrayed our lord by ignoring his Chosen. I speak; you obey.
You ought to be worried about your own hide.
Have you come to dredge up an ancient grudge, Karlach? Now? When so much hangs in the balance?
Goodbye, Karlach.

EditorData.NodeContext: Hostile, but not combat - just shooing her away.

Text.Value: One benefit of becoming the Archduke of Baldur's Gate is that you have a whole legion of soldiers to worry about that for you.
I was young. You should have been my mentor, not my betrayer.
Yet you sowed chaos at my Iron Throne. You blatantly mocked the terms of my bargain.
Kill him and take his stone. The Grand Design cannot come to pass.
Trust you? That's a good one; tell another.
Take the Netherstone. I deserve the power you promised - even if I have to share it with the likes of you.
Do what he asks. My father's life is in his hands.
With the Netherstones in hand, the brain can't resist us. We will be Absolute, with an infected army at our beck and call.
*Gortash studies you carefully in turn. He is shrewd and headstrong, and he expects the same of you.*
Trust me that your best chance of survival is to kill Orin and retrieve the stone.
How can I trust you now, Gortash? After everything you did to me?
Consider it an invitation then. For you to save your own life before it's too late.
I'd hoped that, by now, you'd manage to demonstrate a little more gravitas. A little leadership.
Unless you want to provoke them, my dear, I suggest you hurry on your way.
From you? I guess nothing. Not anymore.
Turns out I don't want to play your little game. I've had enough of those to last a lifetime.
I did what I had to. I have no regrets.
Listen to yourself, Karlach! Blind to every opportunity.
Give me the stone now, Karlach, or face the black hand of Lord Bane.
If you can't seize power when it's given to you, then you're destined to live as a servant. I do not suffer the same affliction.
The brain awakens. It's time I take matters into my own hands.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Gortash raises his arm, showing his gauntlet. The Netherstone in it gleams. He lowers his arms.

Text.Value: *You spot the hint of a smile. He is testing you - he wants you to refuse.*
You want to kill Orin and retrieve the stone. Trust me.
Well, well well! I was certain you'd scupper our alliance in service of an ancient, petty grudge. You've surprised me.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Gortash raises his arm, showing his gauntlet. The Netherstone in it gleams. He lowers his arms. Then only he speaks the line... [Choices]

Text.Value: That thing in your chest is a blessing I helped you receive. One you're too much of a fool to see.
*You can't penetrate his mind.*
I'll be back, motherfucker. See you soon.
You child. You imprudent wretch. I always knew you were good for nothing - that's why I gave you to Zariel without a second thought.
'Took advantage.' Like you were some waif without a will of her own? You threw your lot in with mine. Willingly. Whatever came next falls at your feet, Karlach.
Dream on.
Take the Netherstone. I deserve the power you promised - even if I have to share it with the likes of you.
Take the Netherstones. I deserve the power you promised - even if I have to share it with the likes of you.
Dearest Karlach. I'd busy myself finding Orin if I were you. I'll still be here for any unfinished business, once you've secured your camp.
Oh. A pity.

EditorData.NodeContext: Genuine disappointment. This is a major turning point cause we are giving him what he asked for - but it was a test. He wanted us to resist.

Text.Value: Please. That thing in your chest made you more powerful than you could ever have dreamed of. I conspired to give you a gift, and you're furious about it.
And now I'm giving you the power to become as a god - a ruler of the realm.
Prove your worth, Karlach. Do not buckle at the slightest pressure. Go on. Refuse me.
I don't give a shit about your agreement.

EditorData.logicalname: LOGIC - Has stones, Orin is dead, prisoners are imprisoned

Text.Value: Fine. Take them.
I'm proud of you, Karlach. Proud of what you've accomplished. And I look forward to working together as allies - equals - from this moment on.
That much is clear. You've stricken out at my Steel Watch for reasons that are utterly incomprehensible.
I gave you a clean slate. A chance to rejoin me for our mutual benefit - again.
Karlach. I was wondering when you'd come.
Our time is short. The elder brain is held beneath the city. We must go to it if we're to control it.
Gods, I can't wait to kill you.
Study Gortash. What are his intentions?
Study Gortash. We can't trust this prick, can we?
Yet you struck my Steel Watch. You blatantly mocked the terms of my bargain.
Your actions sparked the fall of my Iron Throne. Whatever bargain we might have made fell with it.
You better follow through on your end of the deal.
*There is no telling what schemes Gortash could be planning.*
Read Gortash's thoughts.
I had high hopes for you. Ones you've dashed to pieces - again.
That thing in your chest made you more powerful than you could ever have dreamed of. I conspired to give you a gift, and you're furious about it.
This was not the agreement.
Bane wills us to work together.
*Your efforts have no effect.*
I don't have them on me. Give me a little time to retrieve them, and they're yours.

EditorData.logicalname: Question- Party has any stones but she doesn't have them in her inventory

Text.Value: I don't have them on me. Give me a little time to retrieve them, and they're yours.

EditorData.logicalname: Question- Party has any stones but she doesn't have them in her inventory

Text.Value: Thanks to you, I endured more suffering than you could begin to fathom.

EditorData.logicalname: LOGIC - Player does not have Ketheric's stone

Text.Value: I can't change the past - and I'm not even sure I would if I could. Look what you've become: An impressive power in your own right.
Not yet. But you will, when I'm done with you.

EditorData.NodeContext: Cut off as an earthquake starts to rattle the room

Text.Value: Your actions sparked the fall of my Iron Throne. Whatever alliance we might have made fell with it.
The only thing that's about to fall at my feet is you.
You don't know the meaning of the word!

EditorData.NodeContext: Furious - a threat. Cut off as an earthquake starts to rattle the room

Text.Value: Yes! That's the spirit, my dear! Not so long ago you did as you were told, no questions asked.

EditorData.NodeContext: Very pleased with himself, and with the player.

Text.Value: Give me time. Our lord wills it.
You're mistaken. I'd like to finish our business now.
You're a disappointment. Again. I've no use for such a weak ally.
Not if I kill you first.

EditorData.NodeContext: A bit psycho; mock friendliness like 'not if I see you first' but perverted

Text.Value: It was always meant to be like this, Karlach. You and I, ruling side by side. Let a new dawn begin.
Sorry?! You want me to be sorry for helping you gain more power than you've ever known?
Yet Orin still lives, still holds her stone. You blatantly mock the terms of my bargain.

EditorData.NodeContext: Angry - note, 'mock' is present tense on purpose

Text.Value: Don't patronise me. Not after everything you've done.
I'm working on it - but not for your benefit.
That's it? That's all you have to say to me?
You're 'working on it' are you? And what do you have to show for yourself? Nothing!
You've killed Orin - and brought me two Netherstones. It is time, my dear. Time to become what we were meant to be.
There is a vessel to the Morphic Pool, where the brain feeds. I will wait for you there.
*You've discovered all you can.*
A lackey once more, hey, Karlach? Pitiful. Bring your leader if you wish to speak to me. I don't waste time on flunkeys.
The brain awakens - we must act now. Faithful, come forward.
Good-bye Karlach. I didn't miss you before, and I won't miss you now.
You live in a fantasy world. One where everyone is to blame but yourself.
I warned you, Karlach. You could have walked away. But you hunger for petty vengeance won out, didn't it?
I've met venomous snakes I'd be faster to trust. Are you sure about this?
It's over for you, Gortash. Take one last look at me, cause I'm the last thing you'll ever see.
I trusted you once. I was so naive, and you took advantage of that.
You have work to do, my dear.
Then stop acting like a child. The past is done, Karlach. Never to return again. And the present is bearing down on our necks like a hobnailed boot.
I'm sure even you can appreciate that.
Enough of the dramatics. You're nursing a wound long-healed. We had the chance to  do something truly incredible here. Now. Not a short lifetime ago.
Your actions sparked the fall of my Steel Watch. Whatever bargain we might have made fell with it.
Karlach. You brought Ketheric's Netherstone.
Your time in the Hells has toughened you up. Made a worthy partner out of you.
How like you, Karlach. You give in with the slightest bit of pressure.
Orin is in your camp as we speak, committing who knows what unspeakable horrors. Whatever festering grudge you bear toward me is of little importance by comparison.

EditorData.NodeContext: Ready to fight. Staying cool, but a hint of villainy

Text.Value: Truthfully, I have no need for an ally who gives away her power at the first ask. I have enough underlings. I want an equal.
Are you sure we should be trusting him?
You most certainly will.
Read Gortash's thoughts.
Bastard.
Maybe it's just me, but I don't trust someone who worships the god of tyranny to share his power.
I don't care about blame. I care about progress. I care about power. That is why you are a servant and I am a master.
Why in the Nine Hells have you come back here, Karlach? What could you possibly want, after what you've done?!
On the contrary. I made you. That thing in your heart has made you more powerful than you had any right to be. You're welcome.
Attack.
You knew what I was. Yet you were fool enough to think the rules didn't apply to you.
God, it's good to watch you suffer.
Your time in the Hells has taught you nothing. You remain the same impulsive little brute you've always been. I haven't missed you at all, you know - and I won't miss you when you're dead, either.
I'm not giving you anything. If we'll both rule, we can each keep our stones.
Fine. Take it.
We could have moved mountains, we could have shaken the planes. And you chose imperfection.
However little I think of you, you always manage to find a way to make me hate you even more.
I'm not a naive kid anymore. And I don't take orders from you.
The only thing I will hand you is my fist, tyrant. And there will be a sword in it.

EditorData.NodeContext: First line delivered as if it's a snappy comeback. Second line is a necessary amendment in case his meaning wasn' t clear

Text.Value: I am who I'm meant to be. You have nothing to do with it.
Surely none but a boiled turnip would trust the likes of him.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Gortash raises his arm, showing his gauntlet. The Netherstone in it does not gleam, but remains as it is. He lowers his arms.

Text.Value: Hand me the Netherstones and we will rule as one - our Lord Bane commands it.
Hand me the Netherstones, and we will rule as one.

Synopsis:
Dialog with Gortash in his office.
Possible outcomes:
1. You visited Steel Foundry and the destroyed Control Centre - he attacks you.
2. You visited Steel Foundry, didn't destroy the Control Centre, but someone activated Dead Man switch which destroyed Iron T hrone. He attacks you.
3. You visited Iron Throne which caused the destruction of it. He tells you - "I warned you" and then attacks you.
4. You didn't kill Orin.
5. You killed Orin and you have both Netherstones.
6. Fallback node which includes the case where you killed Orin, but didn't bring either of the netherstones.
